The Probability acceptance function given above, prefers accepting states which are lower in energy because of the  factor in the numerator of the exponent. You can simply remove this factor, to make the PAF independent of the difference in energies.
The effect of the difference in energies, , on the PAF can be increased/decreased by increasing/decreasing the base of the exponent as shown below: 
